---
description: Protect environment files from accidental modification or exposure
globs: [".env", ".env.*", ".env.local", ".env.production"]
alwaysApply: true
---

# Env Files — Read-Only

- Never modify .env without user confirmation.
- Never commit env files to version control.
- Never display API key values or secrets.
- Never hardcode secrets in code.

## Project Env Vars

This project uses local file logging; no env vars are required for core functionality. Optional vars (if implemented):

- `BOARD_LOG_PATH` — Override log directory (empty = Application.persistentDataPath)
- `BOARD_DEBUG` — Verbose logging (0/1)

## Adding New Vars

1. Add to .env with empty value and comment.
2. Document in TECH_STACK.md Environment Variables.
3. Update this rule if vars become required.
